Since I'm already on this path, here's Creatures:

18. [[Prime Speaker Zagana]] - Hardly worth mentioning, honestly.
35. [[Corpsejack Menace]] - Doesn't kill it, but is in the deck where it will definitely kill other things.
47. [[Fathom Mage]] - Same deal as Corpsejack Menace, although it does make it smaller as well.
73. [[Master Biomancer]] - This is becoming a theme...
74. [[Scavenging Ooze]] - Large Scooze is an issue, but this still doesn't kill it, only makes it smaller.
83. [[Ghave, Guru of Spores]] - Nerfs strategy AND possibly kills
93. [[Bane of Progress]] - Again, hardly worth mentioning.
94. [[Mycoloth]] - Ooof, this would be a tempo hit. Doesn't kill it, does totally nerf it and gain you a bunch of advantage, however.
98. [[Champion of Lambholdt]] - Nerfs it a bit, doesn't kill.
Where is Walking Ballista and Triskelion?
Not in the top 100. Surprised me too.
They seem to organize by Synergy, not actual numbers.
So that might hurt them there, as they are able to be in any deck, but are only used in a handful of strategies.

And lastly, Artifacts:

51. [[Ramos, Dragon Engine]] - Largely doesn't do much if they're rolling already. Gets rid of one mana activation, basically.
56. [[Everflowing Chalice]] - Your number 1 target in monoblack, probably. Doesn't remove it, just makes it useless.
57. [[Bow of Nylea]] - Again, technically relevant, but not really actually.
94. [[Coalition Relic]] - Could have niche functionality, but really not the slam dunk we're looking for.

No Trike and Walking Ballista here, either!
